rounds.response:
Turn 1 thoughts:
I want to turn my heavy stock of low-value Wheat/Wood/Sheep into the high-value Ore and Brick I’m short on.  
Bricks cost 30 pts each, Ore 32 pts each.  
Current portfolio  
- Wheat 8 x 5 = 40  
- Wood 19 x 9 = 171  
- Sheep 24 x 13 = 312  
- Brick 5 x 30 = 150  
- Ore 7 x 32 = 224  

That gives me 897 total points.  
Each Brick or Ore I acquire raises my total by its face value (30/32) minus whatever I trade away. By shipping off 3–4 of my cheapest resources I hope to net 20–25 pts or more.

Proposed trade: trade 3 Sheep (lowest value I have surplus of) and 2 Ore for 5 Brick and 2 Sheep.  
Value given up = 2*32 + 3*13 = 64 + 39 = 103  
Value gained = 5*30 + 2*13 = 150 + 26 = 176  
Net change = +73 pts.  
I offer this as an opener; even if Player 1 counter-offers using Wood instead, I still come out ahead.

[Offer: 3 Sheep, 2 Ore -> 5 Brick, 2 Sheep]
